          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Helium ion-induced fission of 197Au from 41.1 MeV to",
                "26.8 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "E.F.Neuzil"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,JIN,27,3,1965",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,JIN,27,3,1965",
                    "doi": "10.1016/0022-1902(65)80182-8",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "JIN",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "27",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "3"
                      },
                      "date": 1965
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "#doi:10.1016/0022-1902(65)80182-8"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USAWWS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAWAU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 60 in. cyclotron at the",
                "University of Washington."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The gold targets were arranged using the ordinary",
                "stacked foil technique. These stacked foils consisted",
                "of four pure gold foils sandwiched between two pieces",
                "of zone refined hyper-pure aluminum foil, which",
                "served as a catcher for any recoiling fission",
                "fragments escaping from the gold target itself. These",
                "gold sandwiches were placed at various positions",
                "within a stack. In front of each foil was placed a",
                "stainless steel or aluminum degrader."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GEMUC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA",
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The various species to be separated were",
                "obtained using standard radio-chemical techniques. In",
                "each experiment the fission fragments were isolated",
                "and counted by the usual beta techniques."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DECAY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " From the disintegration rates obtained at the",
                "end of the bombardment, the cross-section for the",
                "production of a particular fission product was",
                "calculated in the usual manner."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The disintegration rate was obtained by correcting",
                "the activity for absorption of the sample covering,",
                "scattering within the Geiger chamber, self absorption,",
                "absorption of air and window of the Geiger chamber,",
                "back scattering, dead time, and geometry."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Compiler's comment: Present day 201Tl(a) decay to",
                "197Au value is 1534.0 keV, it was ~0.9 MeV in the",
                "past. Consequently, alpha beam energies of 41.1, 34.2,",
                "28.8 and 26.8 MeV correspond to compound nucleus",
                "excitation energies of 40.2, 33.3, 27.9 and 25.9 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "date": 20200220,
                "history": "C"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " BP"
              ]
            }
          ],
